<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870521-0137 </DOCNO><HL> Turner Broadcasting PlansTo Extend Note Maturity</HL><DD> 05/21/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> TBSBOND MARKET NEWS (BON) </IN><DATELINE> ATLANTA  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Turner Broadcasting System Inc. said it will extend to Sept. 15 from June 15 the maturity date of its $150 million principal amount of extendable senior notes outstanding.    The cable broadcasting concern said the interest rate for the period between June 15 and Sept. 15 will be 15% annually. The current rate on the notes, issued in connection with the company's acquisition of MGM/UA Entertainment Co., is 14 1/2%. </TEXT></DOC>